From: Claude (audit_20260522)
Date: 2026-05-22
Subject: [PATCH] backtest: SCORE-TIER marginal trail dispatch

Add SCORE-TIER marginal trail dispatch to backtest/v5_backtest.py so
marginal-score entries (raw_score < SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD) trail with the
aggressive _MARGINAL_TRAIL profile instead of the swing trail — matching
execution/executor.py:_resolve_trail_steps step 0 + _MARGINAL_TRAIL.

Task spec items (audit_20260522):
  1. Config-driven threshold (default 7.0) + tighter EarlyLossCut params
  2. Entry-path dispatch: raw_score < 7.0  →  use _MARGINAL_TRAIL
  3. _MARGINAL_TRAIL profile (verbatim from executor.py)

Already in HEAD (committed concurrently as 06784f4
  "BT-live parity: model LOSS_STREAK + PEAK_GIVEBACK + EarlyLossCut tiered
  + POST_BIG_WIN"):
  • SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD (default 7.0) loaded from live config
  • EARLY_EXIT_{MARGINAL,SWING}_{TRIGGER_R,CYCLES} constants
  • MARGINAL_TRAIL profile constant (verbatim copy from executor.py)
  → satisfies task items 1 and 3.

Added by THIS patch (task item 2):
  • In backtest_symbol() just before `# Simulate trail`, dispatch to
    MARGINAL_TRAIL when 0 < raw_score < SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD.
  • raw_score is the pre-quality_div 0-12 score from
    _score_with_components — matches live's raw-score-units threshold.

Verifiable:
  $ git apply --check audit_20260522/bt_score_tier_patch.diff   # exit 0
  $ git apply audit_20260522/bt_score_tier_patch.diff
  $ python3 -B backtest/v5_backtest.py --symbol XAUUSD          # smoke

Notes:
  - DOES NOT modify simulate_trail() signature (HEAD already added
    is_marginal=… plumbing there — orthogonal to this trail-profile swap).
  - DOES NOT modify v5_backtest.py outside the single hunk shown below.
  - `_score_tier` local is set for journal/exit-reason annotation if a
    follow-up wants to log the tier (no downstream consumers added here).

---

diff --git a/backtest/v5_backtest.py b/backtest/v5_backtest.py
index 30631fb..80dcc7d 100644
--- a/backtest/v5_backtest.py
+++ b/backtest/v5_backtest.py
@@ -1112,6 +1112,21 @@ def backtest_symbol(symbol, days=90, params=None, verbose=True):
         else:
             adapted_steps = _trail_base

+        # ── SCORE-TIER DISPATCH (2026-05-22) ──
+        # Marginal-tier entries (raw_score < SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD) get the
+        # aggressive MARGINAL_TRAIL instead of the swing trail. Mirrors
+        # executor._resolve_trail_steps step 0. Note we use `raw_score`
+        # (the 0-12 momentum-scorer output) rather than `signal_quality`
+        # (the 0-100 rescaled value) because the live threshold is defined
+        # in raw-score units. Without this dispatch the BT overstates
+        # marginal-bucket winners and understates losers because the swing
+        # trail lets them run too far before locking.
+        if 0 < raw_score < SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD:
+            adapted_steps = MARGINAL_TRAIL
+            _score_tier = "MARGINAL"
+        else:
+            _score_tier = "SWING"
+
         # Simulate trail
         # 2026-05-22: thread is_marginal (raw_score < SCORE_TIER_THRESHOLD)
         # so simulate_trail can dispatch the EarlyLossCut tier (-0.3R/1bar
</content>
</invoke>
